desc=J'ai une petite demande &#xE0; vous faire, Je suis &#xE0; la recherche de fourrure pour cet hiver. &#xC7;a serait d&#xE9;plaisant d'attraper froid en se tuant au travail. Cette fourrure devrait &#xEA;tre bien chaude. Il y a des Wild Boars ici, &#xE0; Weedridge, Apr&#xE8;s avoir collect&#xE9; la fourrure des Wild Boar, je l'emm&#xE8;nerai moi m&#xEA;me &#xE0; Kyra. Elle m'en fera un manteau bien chaud &#x2026; Houhou, j'en suis d&#xE9;j&#xE0; toute excit&#xE9;e 
runDlg=Vous n'avez pas encore termin&#xE9; ?? Je veux le porter aussi vite que possible 
finishDlg=Oh ! C'est de la bonne qualit&#xE9; ! Merci
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Wild Boar's fur collection
desc=I have a request to you. I look for some fur to use in this winter. Leader is likely to catch cold because of heavy work. The fur should be warm.  There are  Wild Boars here Weedridge. After collecting  Wild Boar's fur, I'll take the fur to Kyra. Then she'll give me a warm fur coat. Ha ha, I'm already excited.
runDlg=Isn't this finished yet?? I want to put on as soon as possible
finishDlg=Oh!  This is good of quality.
</newversion></questtextxml></nwarri007><nexp007><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Chassez le Wild Boar 
desc=Ah, vous arrivez juste &#xE0; temps. Nous avons une petite chose &#xE0; vous demander. Le nombre de Wild Boars ne cesse d'augmenter &#xE0;  Weedridge. Ils deviennent une vraie menance. Ces Wild Boars d&#xE9;truisent nos b&#xE2;timents et tourmentent les habitants. Nous sommes des villageois au m&#xEA;me titre que les autres, c'est pourquoi j'invoque votre aide. Allez chasser ces Wild Boars.
runDlg=Ce n'est pas encore termin&#xE9; ? Faites vite, &#xE7;a ne peut pas attendre. 
finishDlg=Bon travail. Je vous donnerai un petit quelque chose. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunting Wild Boar 
desc=Ah, you came in time when we are going to request. Wild Boars are increasing in Weedridge. They're a holy terror. These Wild Boars destroy structures and harass people repeatedly.  We are also same villagers, so I want you to help. Go eliminate Wild Boars.
runDlg=Isn't it finished yet? This is nothing to take time. 
finishDlg=Good job. I'll give you the reward. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nexp007><nexp008><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte des dents de Tough Wild Boar
desc=Hum ... bon, est ce que je peux vous demander un petit service ? Il y a quelques trucs que j'aimerai bien avoir. J'ai demand&#xE9; &#xE0; Mark mais il a refus&#xE9;, pretextant qu'il &#xE9;tait trop occup&#xE9;. Je compte donc sur vous pour m'apporter ce que je veux. Il s'agit des dents de Tough Wild Boar. J'ai d&#xE9;j&#xE0; ma petites id&#xE9;es sur leur future utilisation. S'il vous pla&#xEE;t, apportez moi ces dents deTough Wild Boar.
runDlg=Hein ? Pas encore ? Je vous donnerai une petite r&#xE9;compense pour vos efforts. 
finishDlg=Merci ! Honnetement, je ne m'attendais pas &#xE0; cette r&#xE9;action de la part de Mark !  Pourquoi les hommes ignorent-ils toujours l'avis des femmes ?
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collecting Tough Wild Boar's tooth 
desc=Um..well, may I ask you this request? There are some stuff I want to get. So I asked Mark but he refused, saying he was busy. I hope you bring the stuff. That is Tough Wild Boar's tooth. I have a plan that decorates these after collecting. Please, bring Tough Wild Boar's teeth.
runDlg=Um? Not yet? I'll give a reward as your effort. 
finishDlg=Thank you. I do never expect Mark's refusal!  Why do men ignore women's mind? 
</newversion></questtextxml></nexp008><nexp009><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Chasse de Devil Walker  
desc=Il y a un groupe de d&#xE9;mons appel&#xE9;s  Devil Walker bas&#xE9; dans la Demon Valley au nord Ouest de Weedridge. Ils nuient aux passants et leur d&#xE9;robent leurs biens commerciaux. J'ai entendu parler de vos exploits remarquables aupr&#xE8;s de Kyra. J'esp&#xE8;re que vous r&#xE9;aliserez cette mission avec autant de brillo. Allez chasser ces Devil Walkers. Bien sur, vous efforts seront dignement r&#xE9;compens&#xE9;s. 
runDlg=Si vous n'&#xE9;liminez pas les  Devil Walkers, les commercants ne pourront jamais transporter leurs biens en toute s&#xE9;curit&#xE9;. 
finishDlg=Bon travail. En effet, Kyra ne s'&#xE9;tait pas tromp&#xE9;e. Voici votre r&#xE9;compense. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunting Devil Walker  
desc=There is a group of evil called Devil Walker in Demon Valley at the northwest of Weedridge. They harm passersby and rob of goods for trade. I heard about your remarkable activities from Kyra. So I believe you'll deal with this mission well. Go eliminate Devil Walkers. Of course, the reward will be enough. 
runDlg=Without eliminating Devil Walkers, traders could never transport goods safely. 
finishDlg=Good job. Indeed, you deserve to be praised from Kyra. Here is your reward. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nexp009><nsoula007><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte de l'essence des Wild Boar
desc= Nous, association Divine, continuons nos investigations dans Weedridge. Votre mission, si vous l'acceptez, sera de collecter l'essence des Wild Boar. Une fois que vous aurez trouv&#xE9; l'essence, nous pourrons tirer une conclusion sur les &#xE9;v&#xE8;nements pass&#xE9;s. Partez maintenant et apportez moi ces extraits aussi rapidement que possible. Que Dieu soit avec vous. 
runDlg=Vous avez collect&#xE9; toute l'essence? 
finishDlg=Vous m'avez rapport&#xE9; beaucoup d'essence, bon travail. Laissez moi vous expliquer la suite des &#xE9;v&#xE8;nements. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collecting Wild Boar's essence
desc= We Divine Association continue to investigate about Weedridge. Your job is to collect Wild Boar's essence this time. After collecting the maxium of essence, we'll draw a conclusion what happened. Go collect the essence and bring me as soon as possible. May Spirits bless you all the time. 
runDlg=Did you bring all the essence? 
finishDlg=You brought a lot of essence. Good job. I'll let you know next job right now. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nsoula007><nsoula008><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimination des Tough Wild Boar 
desc=La mission suivant va &#xEA;tre d'&#xE9;liminer les Tough Wild Boar. Les r&#xE9;sultats de mes recherches, comme je m'y attendais, ma conduit &#xE0; cette tragique conclusion : ces cr&#xE9;atures ne peuvent &#xEA;tre domestiqu&#xE9;es. Leurs attaques envers les villageois sont de plus en plus graves. Nous, Association Divine, avons d&#xE9;cid&#xE9; de mettre fin &#xE0; terreur des Tough Wild Boar. Je vous confie cette mission. Avec les esprits et au nom de l'association Divine, &#xE9;liminez les Tough Wild Boars. 
runDlg=Cela doit &#xEA;tre fait, pour qu'enfin l'harmonie r&#xE8;gne encore les hommes et les cr&#xE9;atures.
finishDlg=Je suis ravi que vous ayez termin&#xE9;. Il semblerait qu'il y ait une cause &#xE0; leur violence.L'association Divine essayera d'en d&#xE9;couvrir plus. Bon travail.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminating Tough Wild Boar 
desc=Next mission is eliminating Tough Wild Boar. As a result of my investigation, I knew, it's too late to change them into good stuff. More serious thing is what  they attack villagers. So we Divine Association decided to eliminate Tough Wild Boar. I give you this mission. With Spirits' blessing and the name of Divine Association, eliminate the Tough Wild Boars. 
runDlg=Nothing can be done now for the harmony with other creatures.
finishDlg=I'm pleased you did. There seems to be a reason they get violent. Divine Association will investigate the reason. Good job.
</newversion></questtextxml></nsoula008><nsoula009><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Chasse de Devil Walker 
desc=Il est un lieu appel&#xE9; Demon Valley, au nord Ouest de  Weedridge. Certains pr&#xE9;tendent que les d&#xE9;mons que l'Association Divine traque depuis des jours y vivent. Le chef du village, Mark, a ordonn&#xE9; d'&#xE9;liminer les Devil Walker. C'est bien normal qu'il soit contre ces d&#xE9;mons qui perturbent les villageois. Nous avons donc d&#xE9;cid&#xE9; d'offir notre aide &#xE0; la faveur du village. Rendez vous dans la vall&#xE9;e d&#xE9;moniaque et &#xE9;liminez ces d&#xE9;mons ambulants. Ensuite, vous n'aurez plus qu'&#xE0; vous rendre chez Mark. 
runDlg=Vous &#xEA;tes venu &#xE0; bout de ces Devil Walkers? Ils perturbent la nature, nous voulons aussi les voir disparaitre. 
finishDlg=L'&#xE9;limination de choses contrefaites est une bonne chose pour nous. Gr&#xE2;ce &#xE0; vous, l'&#xEE;le de Cardiff retrouve de son authenticit&#xE9;. J'en suis heureux. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunting Devil Walker 
desc=There is a place named Demon Valley in the northeast of Weedridge. It says that the devil that Divine Association has investigated in these days is living in there. The chief of village, Mark, has longed to eliminate the Devil Walker since long before. It's natural he dislike the devil harassing villagers. So we also plan to help with gratitude in favor of this village. Go to Demon Valley and eliminate Devil Walker. And after that, go to Mark. 
runDlg=Did you eliminate all of Devil Walkers? They are just disrupters of nature we also want to disappear. 
finishDlg=Eliminating what isn't nature is a nice thing in our stance.  Thank to you, Cardiff Island recovers its true self.  So I'm really happy. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nsoula009><nnobi008><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimination de Devil Walker 
desc=Il est grand temps d'&#xE9;liminer les bandits de Weedridge. Le seigneur a d&#xE9;clar&#xE9; la guerre aux Devil Walkers. Nous, nobles, avons donn&#xE9; notre parole : nous le suppl&#xE9;rons dans toutes ses d&#xE9;marches. Allez dans cette vall&#xE9;e d&#xE9;moniaque au Nord Ouest de Weedridge. C'est la bas qe vivent les Devil Walker Tuez les. 
runDlg=S'il vous plait, vous devez aider le village et le seigneur. Cette bataille contre les Devil Walker peut parraitre compliqu&#xE9;e mais elle ne l'est pas. 
finishDlg=Bon travail. Le Seigneur continue de faire appel &#xE0; nous dans la bataille contre les Devil Walker. Je vous informerai de la prochaine mission. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Elimination of Devil Walker 
desc=It's time to eliminate the disrupters of Weedridge. The lord declared a war against Devil walkers, disrupters of Wedridge. So we nobles gave a firm promise about joining the lord and following lord's will. There is Demon Valley in the northwest of Wedridge. the group of Devil Walker is staying there. Go eliminate Devil Walkers. 
runDlg=&#xB9C8;&#xC744;&#xC744; &#xC704;&#xD574;&#xC11C; &#xC601;&#xC8FC;&#xB2D8;&#xC744; &#xC704;&#xD574;&#xC11C; &#xAF2D; &#xC77C;&#xC744; &#xD574;&#xC8FC;&#xC2DC;&#xAE30; &#xBC14;&#xB78D;&#xB2C8;&#xB2E4;. Devil Walker &#xBB34;&#xB9AC;&#xC640; &#xC804;&#xD22C;&#xB294; &#xC870;&#xAE08; &#xC704;&#xD568;&#xD558;&#xAE34; &#xD558;&#xC9C0;&#xB9CC; &#xADF8;&#xB9AC; &#xC5B4;&#xB824;&#xC6B4; &#xC2F8;&#xC6C0;&#xC740; &#xC544;&#xB2D0;&#xAECD;&#xB2C8;&#xB2E4;. 
finishDlg=Good job. The lord keep on requesting we join the war against Devil Walker. I'll let you know about the next mission. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nnobi008><nwarri008><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=&#xC9;limination de Devil Walker Shooter
desc=Le Seigneur a l&#xE9;gitimement demand&#xE9; l'aide de l'association des mercenaires. Le but, c'est d'&#xE9;liminer ces hommes monstrueux, Le Devil Walker vit sur l'&#xEE;le de Cardiff. Cette guerre interminable doit finir par un bon vieux coup de balai ! Alors, commencez par &#xE9;liminer les Devil Walker Shooters. 
runDlg=Laissez place &#xE0; la bagarre contre ces hommes monstrueux ! Faites usages de vos comp&#xE9;tences .. . &#xE0; volont&#xE9; !
finishDlg=Bon travail. Le Seigneur m'a demand&#xE9; de vous remettre cette r&#xE9;compense de sa part. La voici. Il aura certainement plus de choses &#xE0; nous demander par la suite. Je ferai appel &#xE0; vous en temps voulu,
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Devil Walker Shooter Elimination
desc=The lord legally requested a help to mercenary association. The task is to eliminate devil's men, Devil Walker, living in Cardiff island. This long period of battle should be finish this time with a perfect mop up. Well, at first, let's eliminate Devil Walker Shooters. 
runDlg=Now, This is a battle against devil's men. Show your skill as you like. 
finishDlg=Good job. The lord asked me to give you this reward instead. Here it is. He'll continue to request. I want you to come here again.
</newversion></questtextxml></nwarri008><nwarri009><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=&#xC9;limination des Fierce Devil Walker Shooter
desc=Comme je m'y attendais, le seigneur n'arr&#xEA;te pas de faire appel &#xE0; nous. Cette fois ci, il nous demande d'exterminer les Fierce Devil Walker Shooters. Bon, ce n'est pas tr&#xE8;s habituel qu'il fasse appel &#xE0; l'association des Mercenaires, mais c'est une bonne chose pour nous, Gr&#xE2;ce &#xE0; &#xE7;a, on pourra gagner sa confiance. Maintenant, finissez votre mission. 
runDlg=Vous n'avez pas encore termin&#xE9; ? Ne faites pas attendre le seigneur !
finishDlg=Merci pour votre rapidit&#xE9; ! Le seigneur a laiss&#xE9; un cadeau pour vous. Ici. Prenez &#xE7;a avec vous. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Fierce Devil Walker Shooter Elimination
desc=As expected, the lord is requesting continuously. This time he requests the elimination of Fierce Devil Walker Shooters. Well, it's not common he makes these many requests to us, Mercenary Association. It's nice thing for us to receive these requests, and moreover we can also gain confidence. Now, go complete this mission. 
runDlg=Isn't this finished yet? Don't make the lord wait. 
finishDlg=Thanks for your quick handling. The lord gave you a reward. This is your portion. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nwarri009><nwarri010><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=&#xC9;limination de Devil Walker Harpooner 
desc=L'influence des Devil Walkers s'est affaiblie, mais certains monstres s'accrochent. Ceux que l'on nomme  Devil Walker Harpooner attaquent les gens avec leurs harpons ! Beaucoup de villageois souffrent de ces attaques. Le seigneur a fait appel &#xE0; nous, l'association des Mercenaire, pour les &#xE9;liminer. Faites vite, la bataille contre les Devil Walker touche &#xE0; sa fin. 
runDlg=Vous y arrivez ? Tout d&#xE9;pend de vous, demandez de l'aide autour de vous. 
finishDlg=Les harponneurs ont bien &#xE9;t&#xE9; &#xE9;limin&#xE9;s. Le seigneur m'a confi&#xE9; votre r&#xE9;compense. Prenez la. Ah, et Jeremiah vous attend. Allez le voir 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Devil Walker Harpooner Elimination 
desc=Devil Walkers' influence becomes weak, but there are still some strong creatures. They,  so called Devil Walker Harpooner, attacked people with harpoon. So villagers are suffering from this attack. The lord also requested us, Mercenary Association, their elimination. Eliminate them because the battle against Devil Walker is almost finished. 
runDlg=Isn't it going well?  If it is beyond your ability, ask your colleagues for help around here. 
finishDlg=Harpooners are perfectly eliminated. The lord puts a reward to me. Here it is. Ah, Jeremiah is looking for you. Go to her. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nwarri010><nwarri011><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte d'oeil de Mad One-eyed Bat 
desc=Les chauves-souris qui vivent dans les mines abandonn&#xE9;es de Cardiff ont attaqu&#xE9; les mineurs ! C'est devenu impossible de collecter les minerais. Tout le commerce de l'ile &#xE9;tait bas&#xE9; sur l'exportation de ces pierres pr&#xE9;cieuses, mais &#xE0; cause de ces satan&#xE9;es chauves-souris, le commerce de l'ile risque de s'effondrer ! Pour revitaliser ce commerce, nous devons continuer l'exploitation de la mine. Allez &#xE9;liminer les  Mad One-eyed Bat. Apportez moi leur yeux, en preuve de leur &#xE9;limination. 
runDlg=J'aimerai &#xE0; nouveau voir un commerce  fleurissant sur Cardiff Island. 
finishDlg=Bon travail. Je sais que &#xE7;a n'a pas &#xE9;t&#xE9; facile, mais merci pour tout. Tiens, ta r&#xE9;compense. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The collection of Mad One-eyed Bat's eye  
desc=Bats living in Cardiff Abandoned Mine attacked miners. So it is impossible to collect minerals now. We have exported many minerals to other island, but  owing to bats, Cardiff Island's source of income is decreasing now. For revitalizing Cardiff Island's trade, we must reuse Cardiff Abandoned Mine's resource. Go eliminate Mad One-eyed Bat. Bring bat's eye as a token of elimination. 
runDlg=I'd like to see that fully energetic trade is increasing in Cardiff Island. 
finishDlg=Good job. This was a hard task, but thanks for your effort. I'll give you a reward. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nwarri011><nwarri012><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Chasse des Carrier Mole ouverte 
desc=Nous avons un autre probl&#xE8;me dans les mines. Les Carrier Moles volent toutes les denr&#xE9;es. On dit qu'ils volent les paquets des villageois et qu'ils r&#xF4;dent autour du village. Une fois de plus, rendez vous dans les mines abandonn&#xE9;es de Cardiff et &#xE9;liminez ces taupes. Nous devons &#xEA;tre s&#xFB;rs que plus rien ne pourra barrer notre route !
runDlg=Beaucoup de commer&#xE7;ant souffrent des d&#xE9;g&#xE2;ts caus&#xE9;s pas les taupes. &#xC9;liminez les, il en va de la puissance de Cardiff Island. 
finishDlg=Vous avez fait du bon travail. Je vois que Cardiff Island commence d&#xE9;j&#xE0; &#xE0; retrouver sa beaut&#xE9; d'an-temps
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunting Carrier Mole 
desc=There is another problem in the mine. Carrier Moles are stealing the trade goods. It is said that they have taken villagers' bundles, loitering  around the village. Go one more to Cardiff Abandoned Mine and eliminate these moles. We must be sure to remove these obstacls. 
runDlg=There are many traders that are damaged by the moles. Please eliminate them for a vibrant Cardiff Island. 
finishDlg=You did a good job. We could see a vibrant Cardiff Island again. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nwarri012><nexp010><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimation de Devil Walker Harpooner 
desc=Ah, cette mission pemettra d'&#xE9;valuer votre talent. Il y a des Devil Walker Harpooners pas tr&#xE8;s loin des groupes de Devil Walker. Ils sont dou&#xE9;s et capables d'esquiver vos attaques tout en r&#xE9;pliquant fermement. Je pense qu'un Explorer aussi dou&#xE9; que vous peut mettre &#xE0; terre de tels ennemis. Vous apprendrez par la m&#xEA;me occasion &#xE0; combattre un monstre du m&#xEA;me niveau que le votre. Eliminez les Devil Walker Harpooners. Ils repr&#xE9;sentent un d&#xE9;fis important, mais montrez que vous, explorers, &#xEA;tes dot&#xE9;s de comp&#xE9;tences incroyables.
runDlg=Des ennemis puissants ne peuvent que vous rendre plus fort. Il est plus important de vous frotter &#xE0; ce genre de d&#xE9;fis. Faites de votre mieux.
finishDlg=Finalement, vous avez gagn&#xE9; comme je m'y attendais. C'est important d'apprendre petit &#xE0; petit afin de pouvoir r&#xE9;utiliser ces techniques plus tard. Gardez cette exp&#xE9;rience dans un coin de votre t&#xEA;te. Plus tard, devant un combat similaire, cela vous sera d'une grande aide. Mark vous attend. Commencez par aller le voir. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminating Devil Walker Harpooner 
desc=Ah, this mission is for testing your ability. There are Devil Walker Harpooners in a group of Devil Walker. They have a great skill, capable of avoiding quickly and hit correctly. You are an Explorer, and then, I think, you have to learn how to fight against a similar level of enemy. Eliminate Devil Walker Harpooners. They'll be formidable to you, but show you explorers are more excellent .
runDlg=Formidable enemies but you'll be more excellent. Most important thing is your real ability in these kinds of fight. Do your best.
finishDlg=At last you won as I expected. It's important to learn one by one and use in actual fight, if you want to master battle skills. Keep this experience in your mind. When going through a similar battle later, this will be a great help to you. Mark looks for you. Go to him at once. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nexp010><nexp011><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte de c&#x153;urs de Strong Devil Walke
desc=Merci d'&#xEA;tre venu aussi vite. Il s'est produit quelque chose de grave. Plusieurs villageois se sont retrouv&#xE9;s n&#xE9; &#xE0; n&#xE9; avec des Devil Walker. Gr&#xE2;ce &#xE0; vos exploits ainsi qu'&#xE0; ceux de l'association des Mercenaires, il n'&#xE9;tait pas difficile d'&#xE9;liminer ce groupe de Devil Walker. Mais cette fois ci, ils ont contre-attaqu&#xE9; de mani&#xE8;re inattendue. Pire encore, nous avons d&#xE9;couvert un  groupe encore plus fort un peu plus loin. Nous avons envoy&#xE9; des gardes, mais tous sont morts au combat. Allez pr&#xE8;s des Strong Devil Walkers et pourrissez les. Je veux voir leurs coeurs pour croire en leur &#xE9;limination !
runDlg=Etre fort ne fait pas tout. D&#xE9;truisez les en usant d'astuce.
finishDlg=En effet, ce sont bien leurs c&#x153;urs que voila. D'accord, je vais vous donner une r&#xE9;compense. Ah ! Et passez voir Jeremiah avant de partir. Il vous attend. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collecting Strong Devil Walker's Hear
desc=Thank you for your quick arrival. Something urgent came up. Several villagers fighted against Devil Walker. Thanks to your and Mercenary Association's exploits, we could easily eliminate the group of Devil Walker. But they counterattacked unexpectedly this time. And there is a more strong group among Devil Walkers. So we were off guard and defeated easily. Go to Strong Devil Walkers and eliminate them. Bring the strong heart as a token of elimination.
runDlg=Being strong is not all. Eliminate them with your marksmanship.
finishDlg=Indeed, these are their hearts. OK, I'll give you a reward as your exploits. Ah, go to Jeremia, before you leave. She is looking for you. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nexp011><nexp012><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Retrouvez les biens commerciaux vol&#xE9;s 
desc=Merci d'&#xEA;tre venu aussi vite. Pendant le voyage de biens commerciaux dans les Mines Abandonn&#xE9;es de Cardiff, des affaires de cambriolages ont &#xE9;clat&#xE9;. Il semblerait que les Carrier Moles d&#xE9;robent tous nos biens. Ben bien sur, c'est toujours plus simple de voler que de travailler &#xE0; la sueur de son front. Allez nous d&#xE9;barasser des ces Carrier Moles et rapportez moi les paquets dans lesquels ils ont mis tous les biens d&#xE9;rob&#xE9;s. 
runDlg=Une rumeur affirme que ces b&#xEA;tes ne font pas que voler les passants, on dit qu'ils se font &#xE9;galement attaquer. Soyez prudent ! 
finishDlg=Quel effort ! Il y avait bel et bien toutes nos poss&#xE9;ssions dans les sacs. Nous serons sur nos gardes &#xE0; l'avenir quand il s'agiera de transporter des objets d&#xE9;stin&#xE9;s au commerce. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collecting Stolen trade goods 
desc=Thank you for quick arrival. During transporting trade goods in Cardiff Abandoned Mine, the cases of burglary are frequently happening. Perhaps Carrier Moles seem to steal trade goods. Because stealing is easier than making themselves. Go eliminate Carrier Moles and bring their bundles. I guess that there are stolen trade goods in the bundles. 
runDlg=There is a rumor that they even attack people as well as stealing trade goods. Be careful! 
finishDlg=You made a great effort. There were all stolen trade goods, as anticipated. In the future when transporting trade goods, we'll takeguar safety measures about guard of these moles. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nexp012><nsoula010><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte des extraits de d&#xE9;mon 
desc=Une fois de plus, nous avons une mission &#xE0; vous confier concernant l'&#xE9;limination des Devil Walkers. Collectez leur essence. Nous voulons savoir pourquoi ils occupent Cardiff Island. Allez tuer tous les Devil Walkers que vous rencontrerez et apportez moi des &#xE9;chantillons. 
runDlg=Vous m'avez rapportez les &#xE9;chantillons ? J'aurai pr&#xE9;f&#xE9;r&#xE9; &#xE9;couter ce que les esprits avaient &#xE0; dire &#xE0; ce propos. 
finishDlg=Wow, vous m'avez rapport&#xE9; pas mal d'&#xE9;chantillons. Vous vous &#xEA;tes vraiment surpass&#xE9;. Je vais fournir cette information &#xE0; l'Association Divine. Je me demande ce que les esprits en penseront. Mr Mark vous attend. Il semblerait qu'il ait des affaires importantes &#xE0; vous confier. Vous feriez mieux d'aller lui faire un petit coucou.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The essence of the devil Collection 
desc=Now you should do one more mission besides eliminating Devil Walkers. That is to collect the essence of devil from Devil Walker. We plan to confirm why they are staying in Cardiff Island. Go eliminate all the visible Devil Walkers. And bring their essence from them. 
runDlg=Did you bring lots of essence? I'd better listen to stories about them from spirits. 
finishDlg=You brought lots of essence. You really did best. I'll deliver this information to Divine Association. I wonder what spirits say. Mr. Mark is calling you. He looks like having some urgent bussiness. You'll be better to go to him. .
</newversion></questtextxml></nsoula010><nsoula011><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimination de Fierce Devil Walker Shooter
desc=Ah, vous &#xEA;tes la fameuse personne qui a r&#xE9;ussi &#xE0; gagner la confiance de Jaime ? Je vous ai appel&#xE9; pour un travail urgent. Nous avons d&#xE9;clar&#xE9; la guerre contre les Devil Walker, parce que l'ambiance ici ne faisait qu'empirer. Je suis enthousiasm&#xE9; &#xE0; l'id&#xE9;e d'exterminer les touble f&#xEA;te, surtout que vous et plusieurs experts ont ralli&#xE9; notre cause dans l'&#xE9;limination des Devil Walker. Plusieurs forces pr&#xE9;parent donc l'attaque surprise. D'accord, mais, qui gagnera face &#xE0; nos exprets ? Allez tuer les Fierce Devil Walker Shooters.
runDlg=Ce n'est pas encore termin&#xE9; ? Prenez votre temps, le travail ne sera pas si difficile. 
finishDlg=Bien. En effet, personne ne peut nier le talent de nos hommes. Ah, j'ai encore quelque chose &#xE0; vous demander. Faites une petite pause, le travail sera plus dur. Venez me voir quand vous serez pr&#xEA;t.. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Fierce Devil Walker Shooter Elimination
desc=Oh, Are you the person who wins Jaime's confidence? I called you for an urgent thing. We declared a war against Devil Walker, as you know the atmosphere. I am very pleasant in thought that eliminates the disrupters of village long before, and you and several experts joined us for eliminating Devil Walker. Several fierce stuff seems to prepare a surprising attack. Well, but, who wins our experts?  Go eliminate Fierce Devil Walker Shooters.
runDlg=Not yet? Take you time. It's not a hard job. 
finishDlg=Good. Indeed no one can be a match for our talented men. Ah, I have a request. Please wait just a while. This is a hard task a little. If you make up your mind, say to me. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nsoula011><nsoula012><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collection de harpons de Devil Walker Harpooner
desc=Vous &#xEA;tes pr&#xEA;t ? Cette mission sera peu &#xEA;tre un peu plus hardue. Vous devrez m'apporter quelques armes de Devil Walker Harpooner. Bien s&#xFB;r, nous pouvons aussi fabriquer des armes nous m&#xEA;me, mais en prendre des d&#xE9;j&#xE0; existantes nous permettra de faire des &#xE9;conomies. Collectez les armes des Devil Walker Harpooners apr&#xE8;s les avoir &#xE9;limin&#xE9;. 
runDlg=Allez, remplissez vous les poches d'armes. Vous savez, plus y'en a mieux c'est !
finishDlg=Bien. Ah, je vous donnerai une petite r&#xE9;compense pour vos efforts. D'ailleurs, Jaime vous attend, allez le voir. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Devil Walker Harpooner's Harpooner Collection 
desc=Are you ready? This mission is a little too hard. You have to bring Devil Walker Harpooner's weapon. Of course we also make weapons ourselves, but taking  their existing weapons is much better, I think. Collect Devil Walker Harpooners' weapons after eliminating them. 
runDlg=Bring more weapons. You know more is better.
finishDlg=Good. Ah, I'll give you a reward for your effort. And Jaime is looking for you. Go to her ahead. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nsoula012><nsoula013><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte des ailes de Mad One-eyed Ba
desc=Pendant que vous balayiez les Devil Walkers avec Mark, j'ai commenc&#xE9; &#xE0; analyser les actuels probl&#xE8;mes des Mines Abandonn&#xE9;es de Cardiff. Les gens qui s'y sont rendu derni&#xE8;rement disent qu'ils ont vu des chauves-souris cyclopes. Elles n'ont rien de normal. Allez leur aracher les ailes, pour que je puisse voir plus pr&#xE9;cisement quelles mutations elles ont subi. 
runDlg=Les secrets de l'&#xEE;les de Cardiff s'estompent au fur et &#xE0; mesure de mes recherches. 
finishDlg=Bon travail, je vais continuer &#xE0; r&#xE9;colter les informations que vous m'apporterez. Jeremiah a besoin de votre aide. Allez y, et offrez lui main forte. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collection of Mad One-eyed Bat's wings
desc=While you swept Devil Walkers with Mark, I began to investigate the problems that happened in Cardiff Abandoned Mine. The people who went the abandoned mine said that they had seen one eyed bats. The bats will be not a nomal bat. Go collect the bats' wings. I'll confirm what kind of mutant they are. 
runDlg=The secret of Cardiff Island is getting out one by one, as I investigate. 
finishDlg=Good job. I'll continue to collect the informations you brought.  Jeremiah asks you for help. I hope you go to her and give some help. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nsoula013><nsoula014><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte des biens d&#xE9;rob&#xE9;s
desc=Vous &#xEA;tes le nouveau b&#xE9;ni que Jamie a envoy&#xE9;. Ca fait longtemps que j'entends parler de vos exploits alors, j'ai aussi quelque chose &#xE0; vous demander. Un probl&#xE8;me s'est produit lors du transports de biens sur l'&#xEE;le de Cardiff. J'ai entendu dire que les Carrier Moles qui vivent dans les Mines Abandonn&#xE9;es de Cardiff volent souvent nos richesses. Je veux que vous r&#xE9;cup&#xE9;riez les biens d&#xE9;rob&#xE9;s. Votre aide est n&#xE9;cessaire pour retrouver le syst&#xE8;me &#xE9;conomique d'an-temps. 
runDlg=Allez r&#xE9;cup&#xE9;rer les biens commerciaux. 
finishDlg=Vous avez fourni un sacr&#xE9; effort. Merci de nous avoir rendu les biens d&#xE9;rob&#xE9;s.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collection of stolen trade goods 
desc=You're the new summoner Jamie sent.I heard your exploits for a long time. So I made a request. A problem occurred while transporting Cardiff Island's trade goods. I heard Carrier Moles who live in Cardiff Abandoned Mine frequently stole trade goods. I want you to get the stolen good back. Your help is surely necessary for active trade of Cardiff Island. 
runDlg=Take the stolen trade goods again. 
finishDlg=You've got a great effort. Thank you for the recovery of the stolen goods.
</newversion></questtextxml></nsoula014><nnobi009><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte d'armes de Devil Walker Shooter
desc=La mission consiste &#xE0; d&#xE9;pouiller les Devil Walkers de leurs armes. Ils se d&#xE9;fendent bien, mais si nous arrivons &#xE0; leur voler, ils seront beaucoup plus faibles, non ? Le Seigneur veut que vous vous en chargiez. Le Seigneur a &#xE9;galement inform&#xE9; le forgeron Mark que si vous parvenez &#xE0; les apporter, nous pourrions les raffiner. Tr&#xE8;ve de blabla, cherchez les armes, et donnez les &#xE0; Mark. Il saura quoi en faire. 
runDlg=Essayez de collecter le plus d'armes possible. Mark ne pourra ainsi fabriquer plus d'armes. 
finishDlg=Oh, les armes des Devil Walkers. J'en ai entendu parler. Mais je pense que je ne pourrai rien en faire, &#xE9;tant donn&#xE9; qu'elles ont d&#xE9;j&#xE0; &#xE9;t&#xE9; utilis&#xE9;es avant. Bon travail tout de m&#xEA;me. Retournez chez Roderick, il aura certainement une autre mission pour vous. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collection of Devil Walker Shooter's weapon 
desc=This mission is to deprive Devil Walkers of their weapons. They also use weapons, but if we take their weapons, their potential weaken, right? The lord wants  you to take the weapons. The lord also said to blacksmith Mark that if you bring them, make him smelt the weapons inversely. Take their weapons and give them to Mark. He'll smelt them into useful weapons. 
runDlg=It's better you collect as many weapons as possible. Then Mark can make more weapons. 
finishDlg=Oh, Devil Walkers' weapons. I heard about it from the lord. But I don't feel like making them, because of those weapons that devils have been using. Good job. To go to Roderic one more time. Perhaps he will continue to look for you. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nnobi009><nnobi010><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=L'&#xE9;limination des Strong Devil Walker 
desc=D&#xE8;s que les villageois ont commenc&#xE9; &#xE0; attaquer les Devil Walker, des d&#xE9;mons plus puissants encore ont contre-attaqu&#xE9; ! Heureusement, il n'ont pas caus&#xE9; de gros dommages mais le grand Seigneur est en col&#xE8;re. Il a d&#xE9;clar&#xE9; qu'il &#xE9;tait inadmissible que de tels d&#xE9;mons vivent. Il a demander de rechercher un expret pour les &#xE9;liminer. Je pense que vous &#xEA;tes notre homme, j'en suis m&#xEA;me certain. S'il vous plait, &#xE9;liminez ces stupides Strong Devil Walkers. Je sais que vous &#xEA;tes assez fort pour vous lever contre eux. 
runDlg=Vous &#xEA;tes aussi puissant, voire plus que vos ennemis, mais faites tout de m&#xEA;me attention !
finishDlg=Bon travail, ces b&#xEA;tes sont f&#xE9;roces. Le Seigneur vous r&#xE9;clame, allez le voir. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The elimination of Strong Devil Walker 
desc=As soon as you and villagers hit the group of Devil Walker, stronger devils in the group of Devil Walkerd tried to counterattack. Fortunately, there wasn't serious damage but the great lord is enraged, saying that he would naver allow such devils. And he asked me for looking for an expert to eliminate them.  Indeed you are the right man. It's easy to preform. Please, eliminate those stupid Strong Devil Walkers. You could stand against them enough. 
runDlg=You could stand against enough, but be careful. 
finishDlg=Good gob. They are trivial creatures. The lord looks for you. Go to him one time. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nnobi010><nnobi011><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimination de Fierce Devil Walker Shooter 
desc=Ah, Roderick m'a beaucoup parl&#xE9; de vous. Vous nous avez &#xE9;t&#xE9; d'une &#xE9;norme aide lors de la guerre. J'aurai une nouvelle mission pour vous. Le nombre de Devil Walkers ne cesse d'augmenter et d'autres cr&#xE9;atures ont commenc&#xE9; &#xE0; perdre la raison et &#xE0; se comporter comme des chiens enrag&#xE9;s. Ceux la sont de plus en plus rapides et exp&#xE9;riment&#xE9;s. Bien sur, ils ne vous arriveront pas &#xE0; la cheville. Partez &#xE0; la chasse aux Fierce Devil Walker Shooters. Faites leur go&#xFB;ter votre amertume. 
runDlg=Assurez vous de les avoir tous &#xE9;limin&#xE9;. Il faut s'assurer qu'ils ne puisse jamais plus attaquer. 
finishDlg=Ha ha ha. J'&#xE9;tais tellement vex&#xE9; ! A cause de ces voleurs, je ne pouvais plus me concentrer. Gr&#xE2;ce &#xE0; vous, je peux a nouveau retrouver le calme.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The elimination of Fierce Devil Walker Shooter 
desc=Ah, I frequently heard about you from Roderic. You make a significant contribution in the war I declared. So I should have an another request to you. The number of Devil Walkers is continuously decreasing, so several creatures lost their reason and are attacking like a mad dog. But they are faster and very experienced, I heard. Of course, they couldn't be a match for you. go eliminate Fierce Devil Walker Shooters. Let them taste the bitterness. 
runDlg=Sure to eliminate. Never let them damage to us again. 
finishDlg=Ha ha ha, it's very gratifying not to  see the disrupters.
</newversion></questtextxml></nnobi011><nnobi012><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1= L'Elimination des Devil Walker Harpooner 
desc=Vous avez fait de votre mieux pour un travail si difficile ... Mais pour le moment, la guerre contre les Devil Walker n'est pas encore termin&#xE9;e. M&#xEA;me si un nombre tr&#xE8;s important de Devil Walker sont morts, il en reste toujours , reclus dans la for&#xEA;t. Ils se sont m&#xEA;me mis &#xE0; lancer des harpons sur les commer&#xE7;ants. On dirait bien que la gu&#xE9;rilla a commenc&#xE9;. Le pire, c'est qu'ils ont quelque chose dans le cr&#xE2;ne. Votre mission sera d'aller &#xE9;liminer ces Devil Walker Harpooners. Leur extermination est devenue n&#xE9;cessaire. 
runDlg=Bien sur, l'&#xE9;limination des ces brigands n'est pas de tout repos, mais les nobles esp&#xE8;rent de tout c&#x153;ur que vous r&#xE9;ussirez. 
finishDlg=Bon travail. Les derniers petits probl&#xE8;mes devraient &#xEA;tre r&#xE9;gl&#xE9;s rapidement.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The elimination of Devil Walker Harpooner 
desc=You did best for a difficult job. Yet this war against Devil Walker&#xC640;is not over. After a lot of Devil Walker had died, the remnants of them went in the forest, and now, are harming passersby as throwing harpooners. It's kind of guerilla war. They seem clever a little. Your job is eliminating those Devil Walker Harpooners. Well, think of sweeping the remnants like a spotless room. 
runDlg=Of course, the sweeping of the remnants is troublesome work, but for us nobles, we hope you do better than our thought. 
finishDlg=Good job. These trivial problems should be solved whenever it happens.
</newversion></questtextxml></nnobi012><nnobi013><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Chasse de Mad One-eyed Bat 
desc=Laissez moi vous raconter les accidents qui se sont produits ces derniers temps dans les Mines Abandonn&#xE9;es de Cardiff. Un villageois qui passait dans les mines a &#xE9;t&#xE9; attaqu&#xE9; par une chauve-souris. Il a tout de m&#xEA;me reussi &#xE0; s'enfuir mais a gard&#xE9; une cicatrice de l'immondicit&#xE9; de la b&#xEA;te. A en croire les dires du villageois, la chauve-souris n'aurait qu'un oeil. C'est une cr&#xE9;ature mutante ! Eliminez les, &#xE7;a commence &#xE0; me faire de plus en plus peur. 
runDlg=Ce sont des b&#xEA;tes horribles. Balayez les de la lumi&#xE8;re de votre coeur. 
finishDlg=Merci pour tout. Oh, Jeremiah vous attend. On dirait qu'il a quelque chose &#xE0; vous dire. Rendez lui visite. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunting of Mad One-eyed Bat 
desc=Let me tell you about some incident happened in Cardiff Abandoned Mine a few days ago. A villager, who was passing by Cardiff Abandoned Mine, was attacked by a bat. The villager barely saves his life but he's had quite a scare at bat's hideous look. According to the villager, it is said the bat's eye was only one. The creature is a mutant. Please eliminate these bats. That's such a headache more and more. 
runDlg=They are trivial things. Let's sweep with a light heart. 
finishDlg=Thank you for your effort. Ah, Jeremiah is looking for you. There seems something to ask. Go to Jeremiah one time. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nnobi013><nnobi014><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte des biens commerciaux d&#xE9;rob&#xE9;s 
desc=J'ai entendu de par le Seigneur que votre talent n'avait d'&#xE9;gal d'en la r&#xE9;gion. Ces derniers temps, nous avons relev&#xE9; un fort taux de braquages dans les Mines Abandonn&#xE9;es de Cardiff. Nous avons re&#xE7;u l'information selon laquelle les Carrier Moles volaient les biens commerciaux. Allez les &#xE9;liminer et rappoortez moi leurs balotins. Avec un peu de chance, les biens d&#xE9;rob&#xE9;s s'y trouveront. 
runDlg=Le Seigneur d&#xE9;sire veut faire florir le commerce de l'&#xEE;le de Cardiff comme avant. J'esp&#xE8;re que vous pourrez r&#xE9;aliser son souhait au plus vite. 
finishDlg=Bon travail. Vous avez &#xE9;t&#xE9; &#xE0; la hauteur de mes esp&#xE9;rances. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collection for stolen trade goods 
desc=I heard about your ability from the lord. In these days during transporting trade goods, robbery cases are frequently ocurring in Cardiff Abandoned Mine. We get an information Carrier Moles are stealing those trade goods. Go eliminate Carrier Moles and bring the bundles. Perhaps there will be stolen goods in the bundles. 
runDlg=The lord will also want Cardiff Island's trade to become active. I hope you solve the problem in a hurry. 
finishDlg=Good job. You live up to my expectation. 
</newversion></questtextxml></nnobi014><classw001><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Parler avec Kent
desc=Est-ce qu'un d&#xE9;butant comme toi peut avoir une vraie position de Mercenaire ? Non, je crois pas. Si tu gagnes la confiance de Kent &#xE0; Castle hall, j'y r&#xE9;fl&#xE9;chirai peut &#xEA;tre &#xE0; deux fois. 
runDlg=Pour votre meilleur choix ...
finishDlg=Pourquoi t'es encore l&#xE0; ? 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Elimination of all appearing enemies 
desc=Do you rookie aim at Mercenary's position? Not yet. If you gain confidence from Kent in Castle hall, I'll think about it once again. 
runDlg=For your greatest choice&#x2026;
finishDlg=What do you come here for again? 
</newversion></questtextxml></classw001><classw002><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Trouver la token of GUARDIAN
Mission2=Elimination de tous les ennemis visibles 
desc=Tu r&#xEA;ves d'une vie de 'Guardien', mercenaire ? Je peux te donner les qualifications de 'Guardien' si tu veux. Mais pour obtenir le titre de Guardien, tu devras passer un petit test. Pr&#xE8;s d'ici se trouve une &#xEE;le nomm&#xE9;e 'Ron'. La bas, il y a un bon endroit pour se battre. Si tu prends ce symbole de Guardien, des ennemis t'attaqueront. Elimines les. 
runDlg=Bonne chance &#xE0; toi. Une fois ta mission termin&#xE9;e, je pourrai t'apprendre quels sont les autres titres du Mercenaire. 
finishDlg=Bravo, tu t'en es bien sorti. Tu as l'autorisation de porter le titre de 'Guardien'.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Trouver la token of GUARDIAN
Mission2=The elimination of all enemies appearing 
desc=Are you a Mercenary  'GUARDIAN's life'? I'll give you 'GUARDIAN's' qulification if you want. For gaining a title to become GUARDIAN, you should pass my test.  There is an island call 'Ron' nearby. And there is a good place to fight in the island. If you take this token of 'GUARDIAN, enemies will attack you. Eliminate the enemies with this token of GUARDIAN. 
runDlg=Good luck to you. I let you know about Mercenary's another title. 
finishDlg=You have done well. I permit 'GUARDIAN's title.
</newversion></questtextxml></classw002><classw003><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Trouver la Cony Stone
Mission2=Le garde de la pierre de Cony 
desc=L'homme qui pouvait tout bloquer. Nous l'appelons le 'D&#xE9;fenseur'. Voici un petit test pour obtenir le titre de 'D&#xE9;fenseur'. Il est une &#xEE;le appel&#xE9;e Cony pr&#xE8;s de l'&#xEE;le de Magnel. Et voici la pierre de Cony. Si vous emportez la pierre avec vous, des montres vont probablement se ruer sur vous. Votre mission si vous l'acceptez sera de prot&#xE9;ger la pierre de ces monstres. Apr&#xE8;s &#xE7;a, revenez me voir. Je vous offrirai alors le titre de 'Defenseur'. 
runDlg=Bonne chance &#xE0; vous. Il n'est pas bon d'&#xEA;tre un d&#xE9;butant ces derniers temps. 
finishDlg=Bon travail. Tu es comme les rumeurs le disent. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Trouver la Cony Stone
Mission2=The guard of Cony Stone 
desc=The man who blocks all things. We call him 'DEFENDER. There is a test for gaining DEFENDER's title. There is an island called Cony around Magnel Island. And there is Cony Stone, if you take the stone, maybe enemies will crowd into you. Your mission is to guard Cony stone from the enemies. After guarding successfully, come to me. Then I'll give you DEPENDER's' title. 
runDlg=Good luck to you. Nice to be not like rookie. 
finishDlg=Good job. You are as nice as rumors 
</newversion></questtextxml></classw003><classw004><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Rodrigo 
desc=Vous avez aussi gagn&#xE9; le titre de 'D&#xE9;fenseur' maintenant. Choisis toi m&#xEA;me pour le prochain. Ton destin est tout trac&#xE9;. Retournez &#xE0; Glostern pour parler &#xE0; Rodrigo. Peut &#xEA;tre te soumettra-t-il &#xE0; l'&#xE9;preuve finale.
finishDlg=Oh, j'arrive pas &#xE0; le croire. Un d&#xE9;butant ne pourras jamais obtenir ce titre ! 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Rodrigo 
desc=You also acquire DEfENDER's 'title now. Decide yourself about the next. Your fate would be already decided when starting this advanture. Go back to Rodrigo in Glostun. He will probably have a final selection to you.
finishDlg=Oh, I don' believe. A rookie acquires this title! 
</newversion></questtextxml></classw004><classe001><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Crow 
desc=C'est l'heure de d&#xE9;cider de ton destin. Je parlerai &#xE0; Crow &#xE0; Castle Hall, alors rejoignez nous la bas. Ca ne va pas &#xEA;tre facile &#x2026; Votre aventure est tellement exceptionnelle. 
runDlg=C'est une glorieuse destin&#xE9; ! 
finishDlg=Um, j'ai &#xE9;t&#xE9; inform&#xE9; par Ruskin. L'heure de d&#xE9;cider de ton destin a sonn&#xE9;. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The conversation with Crow 
desc=It's time to decide your fate. I'll tell Crow in the Castle Hall, so come here after deciding your fate there. It'll be not easy because of a rough itinerary. 
runDlg=What a nice fate! 
finishDlg=Um, I heard this from Ruskin. You should decide between your two fate from now. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classe001><classe002><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimination de Patus en 11 Minutes 
desc=Si l'on en croit leur developpement, les Explorers choisissent des chemins diff&#xE9;rents. Je ne sais pas le quel tu veux emprunter, mais je vais t'en montrer un. Avant &#xE7;a, je vais devoir te tester. Ignis, r&#xE9;put&#xE9; pour &#xEA;tre l'&#xEA;tre le plus cruel du Lava Plateau est entour&#xE9; de cr&#xE9;atures appel&#xE9;es Patus. Ce sont ses sbires, et les &#xE9;liminer ne sera donc pas chose ais&#xE9;e. Ils sont extr&#xEA;mment vifs et habiles, mais je veux que vous soyez encore plus vif et encore plus habiles qu'eux. Revenez dans les 10 minutes qui suivent et assurez vous d'avoir &#xE9;limin&#xE9; 10 Patuses. Je pourrai ensuite vous confier le titre de CHASSEUR
runDlg=Pas facile, n'est ce pas ? Le r&#xF4;le du chasseur est difficile. 
finishDlg=Bon travail, merveilleux ! Voici le titre de chasseur. Mais un Explorer peut faire autre chose encore. Je veux bien entendu parler du BLASTER. Si tu m&#xE8;nes &#xE0; bien la prochaine mission, tu sauras gratifi&#xE9; du titre de BLASTER. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminating Patus within 16 minutes 
desc=According to his developing direction,  Explorers go their own load, not to the same load. I don't know the load you want, but I'll teach you about one load. I'll test you before that. There is Ignis, known as a dangerous existence, in Lava Plateau. And around the place, there are some creatures named Patus. They are underlings who follow Ignis. It is not easy to eliminate them because their movements are quick and shrewd. But want you to show being more quick and correct than the underlings. Come back with 10 minutes after eliminating 10 Patuses. Then I'll confer the title of HUNTER
runDlg=Not easy, right? HUNTER's role is difficult as much as the ability. 
finishDlg=Good job. Wonderful! I gave HUNTER's title, but an Explorer can do one more thing. That's just BLASTER. If you carry out next imssion, I'll confer the title of BLASTER. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classe002><classe003><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte des c&#x153;urs de Wisp
Mission2=Collecte de fourrures de Flame Crewbarian
Mission3=Collecte des morceaux de Patus
desc=Les Blasters sont souvent capables de voir des choses myst&#xE9;rieuses dans un lieu pourtant anodin. Si tu parviens &#xE0; me rapporter ce que je veux, je te donnerai le titre de BLASTER. Apporte moi des coeurs de Wisp du Lava Plateau, de la fourrure de Flame Crewbarian et des morceaux de Patus. 
runDlg=Vous n'avez pas encore termin&#xE9; ? Hihi, effectivement, ce ne sont pas des choses que l'on trouve facilement. 
finishDlg=G&#xE9;nial ! Comment as-tu fait pour trouver &#xE7;a ? Comme promis, voici le titre de Blaster. Retournez voir Ruskin &#xE0; Glostern. Je le previendrai de votre venue et vous n'aurez qu'&#xE0; choisir entre ces deux titres. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collecting The core of Wisp
Mission2=Collecting Flame Crewbarian's fur
Mission3=Collecting Patus' pieces
desc=Blasters often find mysterious things in the common place. If you fine what I say now in next area, I'll give you BLASTER's title. 
 Wisp's core from Wisp of Lava Plateau, Flame Crewbarian's fur from Flame Crewbarian, Patus' pieces from Patus. 
runDlg=Not yet? Haha, that is not something you find esaily. 
finishDlg=Great! How did you find it? As I promised, I'll give you Blaster's title. Turn back to Ruskin in Glostun. I'll tell him in advance. So you have only  to choose one between the two titles. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classe003><classn001><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Lloyd
desc=On dirait que vous &#xEA;tes venu ici pour la magie surpuissante. Je vais vous pr&#xE9;senter quelqu'un. Son nom est LIoyd et il tient un bar sur la petite &#xEE;le de 'Ron'. Lui seul maitrise le c&#xF4;t&#xE9; cach&#xE9; de la magie et pourra te parler de la magie noire. Il te parlera aussi certainemeent de quelqu'un qui connait la magie blanche. Apprend en plus, alors seulement je pourrai d&#xE9;cider de ton destin.
runDlg=Ce sont deux destins honorables. 
finishDlg=Qu'est ce qui te ram&#xE8;ne sur cette petite &#xEE;le ? 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Lloyd
desc=You seem to come here for mastering magic. I introduce a person to you. His name is Lloyd and runs a bar in an island called 'Ron'. He, who mastered the flipside of magic, will let you know about black magic. And also he introduce a person to you, knowing the magic of directing right path. Master all of the two. Then I'll decide your fate. 
runDlg=This is honorable two fates. 
finishDlg=What's up to this small island? 
</newversion></questtextxml></classn001><classn002><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecte d'un vieux manuscrit 
desc=Ah, vous &#xEA;tes venu ici pour apprendre la face cach&#xE9;e de la magie. Votre esprit n'est pas celui de n'importe quel Noble. Au lieu de t'apprendre ce pourquoi tu &#xE9;tais venu, je vais te demander un petit service. Il y a des Strong Volcano Imps au Lava Plateau de l'&#xEE;le de Magnel. Ces diablotins m'ont vol&#xE9; les pages du livre. Il faut les r&#xE9;cuperer. 
runDlg=Vous devrez &#xE9;liminer beaucoup de diablotins avant de trouver les pages du manuscrit. 
finishDlg=Oh! C'est bien &#xE7;a ! Merci. These are the ones. Thank you. Laisse moi t'enseigner les bases pour devenir 'SOLEKNIGHT'. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The collection of an old magic book 
desc=Ah, you come here for mastering the flipside of magic. Your spirit appears to be not the same for Noble's. Instead of teaching what you want, I'll ask you a request. There are Strong Volcano Imps at Lave Plateau of Magnel Island. Several imps among them have the old magic books. Please, bring the books to me. 
runDlg=Because only several imps have the books, you should eliminate a lot of imps. 
finishDlg=Oh! This is the one. Thank you. I'll let you know about the knowledge of magic I have. Then you'll be qualified for becoming 'SOLEKNIGHT'. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classn002><classn003><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Lady Avery 
desc=Laissez moi vous pr&#xE9;senter quelqu'un qui vous enseignera l'autre voie de la magie. Allez rendre visite &#xE0; Lady Avery sur l'&#xEE;le d'Exeter Island. Elle pourra s&#xFB;rement vous apprendre cette magie myst&#xE9;rieuse. Le Noble apprend naturellement la magie mais elle vous apprendre comment un Noble se doit de l'utiliser.
finishDlg=Vous, vous &#xEA;tes venu me voir pour en apprendre plus &#xE0; propos de la magie des nobles &#x2026; sage d&#xE9;cision.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Lady Avery 
desc=&#xB2E4;&#xB978; &#xB9C8;&#xBC95;&#xC758; &#xAE38;&#xC744; &#xC54C;&#xB824;&#xC904; &#xC0AC;&#xB78C;&#xC744; &#xC18C;&#xAC1C;&#xD558;&#xC8E0;. Exeter Island&#xC758;Lady Avery&#xB97C; &#xCC3E;&#xC544;&#xAC00; &#xBCF4;&#xC2DC;&#xAE30; &#xBC14;&#xB78D;&#xB2C8;&#xB2E4;. &#xADF8;&#xB140;&#xAC00; &#xC544;&#xB9C8; &#xB2E4;&#xB978; &#xB9C8;&#xBC95;&#xC744; &#xAE38;&#xC744; &#xC54C;&#xB824;&#xC904; &#xAC83;&#xC785;&#xB2C8;&#xB2E4;. &#xC815;&#xC2DD;&#xC73C;&#xB85C; Noble&#xC758; &#xB9C8;&#xBC95;&#xC744; &#xBC30;&#xC6B4; &#xADF8;&#xB140;&#xB294; &#xC544;&#xB9C8; &#xC815;&#xB3C4;&#xC758; Noble &#xB9C8;&#xBC95;&#xC5D0; &#xB300;&#xD574;&#xC11C; &#xC54C;&#xB824;&#xC904; &#xAC83;&#xC785;&#xB2C8;&#xB2E4;.
finishDlg=&#xB2F9;&#xC2E0;&#xC740;&#x2026;&#xB098;&#xC5D0;&#xAC8C; &#xADC0;&#xC871; &#xB9C8;&#xBC95;&#xC5D0; &#xB300;&#xD574;&#xC11C; &#xBC30;&#xC6B0;&#xB7EC; &#xC654;&#xAD70;. &#xC798; &#xC624;&#xC168;&#xC18C;
</newversion></questtextxml></classn003><classn004><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Recherche du manuscrit &#xE9;gar&#xE9;
desc=Ce que je suis sur le point de te r&#xE9;v&#xE9;ler est l'histoire que seuls les nobles ayant suivi le droit chemin peuvent entendre. On les appelle les 'MAGES'. Bien sur, je pourrai vous donner ce titre de 'MAGE' imm&#xE9;diatement, maiiis j'aurai un petit service &#xE0; vous demander avant. Il y a tr&#xE8;s longtemps, un noble a &#xE9;gar&#xE9; un manuscrit et d'apr&#xE8;s mes sources, l'Imp Leader aurait r&#xE9;cup&#xE9;r&#xE9; le livre et s&#xE9;journe depuis au Lava Plateau de l'&#xEE;le Magnel.  Apporte le livre et je t'offrirai le titre de MAGE. 
runDlg=J'esp&#xE8;re que tu m'apporteras le livre. 
finishDlg=Merci, d&#xE9;sormais, nous te qualifierons de MAGE. Allez voir Ian et d&#xE9;cidez de votre avenir ! Bonne chance.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Recovering noble's missing book 
desc=What I teach is to be delivered to the nobles who have pursuited only right direction. They are called as 'MAGE'. Of course I could give you 'MAGE's title, but you have to receive a request.  There is a book lost in Noble Masquer a long time ago. I get an information that Imp Leader has the book, staying at Lava Plateau of  Magnel Island.  Bring the book. Then I'll give you MAGE's title. 
runDlg=I wish you would bring the book. 
finishDlg=Thank you. I'll qualify you for MAGE. Go back to Iann and decide you fate. Good luck to you.
</newversion></questtextxml></classn004><classn005><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Ian 
desc=Vous devez choisir entre ces deux titres. Quel que soit votre choix, j'esp&#xE8;re de tout c&#x153;ur que vous n'allez pas le regretter. 
runDlg=Que la magie vous guide.
finishDlg=F&#xE9;licitations, j'esp&#xE8;re que j'ai gloire jalonnera ton futur. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Ian 
desc=You have to choose one among the titles you gained when having an adventure. Whatever you choose, I hope you are not regrettable. 
runDlg=Magic led you. 
finishDlg=Congratulation. I wish the honor is with you in your future. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classn005><classs001><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec le Shaman Puck 
desc=Votre destin est sur le point de se jouer, tout naturellement. C'est l'heure, allez voir le Shaman Puck qui se trouve sur l'&#xEE;le de Cardiff. Peut &#xEA;tre qu'il sera &#xE0; l'origine de votre destin&#xE9;. 
runDlg=La nature chuchotte votre nom. 
finishDlg=Hein ? Qui &#xEA;tes vous ?
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Shaman Puck 
desc=Nature are going to decide you fate. It's time to go. Go to Shaman Puck in Cardiff Island. Perhaps he becomes the man who decide your fate. 
runDlg=Nature is wispering with your name. 
finishDlg=Uh? Who are you?
</newversion></questtextxml></classs001><classs002><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Destruction du Skull Monument dans Fox Den  
Mission2=Elimination des Patus au Lava Plateau
Mission3=Elimination des Tiger Spider &#xE0; Castle Field
desc=Ah, vous &#xEA;tes l'homme qui m'a sauv&#xE9; de mes cauchemars ! Quoi ? Vous voulez dire que vous souhaiteriez devenir SHAMAN comme moi ? Ce n'est pas compliqu&#xE9;, mais je devrai en discuter avec les esprits. Eux seuls peuvent octroyer le droit d'&#xEA;tre capable de la destruction de la nature. Pour avoir le titre de SHAMAN, eliminer les cibles suivantes. D'abord, les Skull Monument dans Fox Den, Patus du Lava Plateau, Tiger Spider &#xE0; Castle Field. 
runDlg=Ressentez la puissance de la nature et des esprits r&#xE9;unis. 
finishDlg=F&#xE9;licitations, je vais vous confier le droit de devenir SHAMAN. Filez chez Ross &#xE0; Castle Hall. Il vous enseignera comment devenir Saint, une autre d&#xE9;stin&#xE9;e.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Destroying Skull Munument at Fox Den  
Mission2=Eliminating Patus at Lava Plateau Patus 
Mission3=Eliminating Tiger spider in Castle Field
desc=Ah, You are the man who rescued me from nightmare. What? Are you saying that you'd like to be SHAMAN like me? It's easy but I should converse with spirits in advance. Spirits only can permit the right that destroy anything from nature's power. For SHAMAN's title, eliminate the following stuff. 
  Skull Monument of Fox Den, Patus of Lava Plateau, Tiger Spider of Castle Field. 
runDlg=Feel nature's and sprit's power togethr. 
finishDlg=Congratulation. I'll give the title as a SHAMAN who I also recognized. Go to Ross at Castle Hall, then he'll say to you Saint's another load. Go to Ross. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs002><classs003><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Ross 
desc=Bienvenue. Vous &#xEA;tes venu ici pour le sort d'antidote ? Ce n'est pas quelque chose de compliqu&#xE9;. Si vous voulez pouvoir soigner du poison, je vous enseignerai comment faire. C'est vrai, le r&#xF4;le des saints est aussi de gu&#xE9;rrir les cr&#xE9;atures malades. Si tu remplis ta mission avec succ&#xE8;s, je t'accorderai le droit de devenir PRIEST. 
finishDlg=Es tu pr&#xEA;t pour ta mission ? 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conservation with Ross 
desc=Welcome. Do you come here for the skill of cure? It's not difficult thing. If you want Saint's skill to cure, I'll teach you the skill especially. Curing ill creatures is also one of Saint's role. If you perfectly perform a mission I want, I'll qualify you for PRIEST. 
finishDlg=Now, are you ready to carry out the mission? 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs003><classs004><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Mark
desc=Mark, qui travaille d'arache pied &#xE0; Roxbury, souffre de terribles mots de ventre et malheureusement, aucun docteur ne semble s'en soucier. Allez le voir et soignez son estomac. Apr&#xE8;s l'avoir soulag&#xE9;, revenez me voir. Nous avons beaucoup de patients &#xE0; soigner ici aussi. 
runDlg=Ooh&#x2026;. Ca faisait longtemps que je n'avais plus vu personne. Tu es venu ici pour m'aider ? 
finishDlg=Oh *-* ! La douleur a disparu. Vous m'avez soign&#xE9; ? Merci beaucoup. Quand as-tu apris de telles comp&#xE9;tences ? En tous cas, merci. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Mark&#xC640; &#xB300;&#xD654;
desc=Mark, working eagerly in Roxbury, is surffering from stomach ache. There seems no doctor. Go to Mark and cure his stomach ache. After curing him, come back here. Here are a lot of patients to cure. 
runDlg=Ooh&#x2026;. Long time no see. Do you come here for help me? 
finishDlg=Uh? Pain's disappeared. Did you cure me?  Thank for this. When did you learn such a skill? Thank you anyway. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs004><classs005><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Lord Lionel 
desc=Maintenant, vous allez devoir soigner le Seigneur Lionel &#xE0; Roxbury. Ce travail est assez d&#xE9;licat, mais je ne peux me permettre de refuser une faveur au dirigeant de Roxbury. Il souffre de migraines depuis peu. Pouvez vous aller le soigner ? 
runDlg=Hein ? Ca faisait longtemps que je n'avais plus vu quelqu'un. On a quelque chose &#xE0; faire ensemble ? 
finishDlg=Quoi ?! Mes migraines se sont compl&#xE8;tement estomp&#xE9;es. C'est g&#xE9;nial, merci ! 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Lord Lionel 
desc=Next you should cure Lord Lionel in Roxbury. This job is a very uninviting thing to do, but I can't just pretend not to know the ruler of Roxbury. He has had headache recently. Go to him and cure. 
runDlg=Uh? Long time no see. Do you have business to me? 
finishDlg=Huh, My headache is clear completely. It's amazing. Thank you. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs005><classs006><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec General Renfield 
desc=La prochaine personne &#xE0; soigner se trouve &#xEA;tre le General Renfield qui vit ici m&#xEA;me. J'ai entendu dire que des champignons poussaient sur ses pieds. Mon radar &#xE0; maladie me dit qu'il faut mieux soigner &#xE7;a avant que les choses n'empirent. Allez soigner ses pieds. Je suis sur qu'il en sera ravi.
runDlg=Hein, qui est-ce ? Que me voulez vous ? 
finishDlg=Oh mon Dieu, comment avez-vous pu soigner mon pied d'athl&#xE8;te ? Comment puis je vous remercier ? 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The conversation with General Renfield 
desc=The next cure is General Renfield living in this village. I heard that he is surffering from athlete's foot. Well, chronic desease is better as quickly as possible. Go and treat the athlete's foot. He sure to be pleasant. 
runDlg=Um, Who is this? What business do you have? 
finishDlg=Oh! Dear. How can my athelete's foot heal completely? How can I say thank you? 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs006><classs007><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Lizzie 
desc=Oh, bon travail. Vous &#xEA;tes bel et bien l'homme que les esprits ont choisi. La prochaine personne &#xE0; soigner s'appelle Lizzie, qui semble &#xEA;tre victime d'une indigestion. Elle a peut &#xEA;tre mang&#xE9; quelque chose qui ne passe pas. Allez voir Lizzie et aidez la.
runDlg=Hein ? Quoi de neuf ? 
finishDlg=Oh, mon cher ! Mon estomac est soign&#xE9;. Vous m'avez soign&#xE9; ? Merci !
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The conversation with Lizzie 
desc=Oh, good job. You are the man who spirits chose, indeed. The next is to cure Lizzie who has indigestion. He maybe eat bad food while cooking a new dish. Go to Lizzie and help her.
runDlg=Uh? What up? 
finishDlg=Oh, dear! My stomach is settled. Did you cure me? Thank you! 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs007><classs008><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Lady Avery 
desc=Le prochain patient se trouve &#xEA;tre une patiente. Lady Avery &#xE0; Glostern se plaint d'un mal de t&#xEA;te atroce. Peut &#xEA;tre qu'elle est victime d'une insolation. Allez la soigner.  
runDlg=Qu'est ce qui vous amm&#xE8;ne ici ?
finishDlg=Oh, je me sens tellement soulag&#xE9;e. Vous m'avez soign&#xE9; ? Je vous remercie. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Lady Avery 
desc=Next patient is the lord Lady Avery in Glostern. Because of heavy work, maybe the lord went around outside for a long time and has heatstroke. Go to her and cure.  
runDlg=What brings you here?
finishDlg=Oh, I feel refreshed again. Did you cure me? Thank you. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs008><classs009><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Roland 
desc=Le prochain patient, Roland se trouve &#xE0; Glostern. Il a &#xE9;t&#xE9; empoisonn&#xE9; par un serpent lors d'une promenade en for&#xEA;. Fais vite pour le soigner, le venin est encore en train de se r&#xE9;pandre dans ses veines. 
runDlg=Aie, s'il vous plait ! Appelez le m&#xE9;decin ! 
finishDlg=Uh, oh&#x2026;On dirait que le poison s'estompe. Vous m'avez soign&#xE9; ? Merci, vraiment !
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Roland 
desc=Next patient is Roland living in Glostern. He was poisoned by snake after going in the forest. Go to him and cure. Hurry up as not to spread throughout the whole body. 
runDlg=Oop, please, call a doctor. 
finishDlg=Uh, oh&#x2026; poison looks like leaving my body. Did you cure me? Thank you, ho, ho! 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs009><classs010><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Discussion avec Jonathan 
desc=Wow, vous vous &#xEA;tes occup&#xE9; des patient malades avec tellement de soin ! Le test est un succ&#xE8;s, vous avez tout se dont un 'PRIEST' a besoin. Maintenant, la d&#xE9;cision vous appartient. Choisissez une voie que vous ne regretterez pas. Allez voir Jonathan &#xE0; Glostern. Il vous guidera sur les traces de la nature. 
runDlg=Soyez b&#xE9;ni par la nature !
finishDlg=F&#xE9;licitation, les voix de la natures vous ont men&#xE9; jusqu'ici. Choisissez votre destin&#xE9;e maintenant. La nature saura choisir pour vous quoi qu'il en soit. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversation with Jonathan 
desc=Wow, you carry out a wonderful cure for ill patients. You fully have a capability for 'PRIEST'. Decreetly get one load not to regret, among the loads Saint could choose. Turn back to Jonathan in Glostun. He'll lead you to nature's load. 
runDlg=Nature bless you! 
finishDlg=Congratulation. Nature's voice led you. Choose your fate now. Nature will lead you to a righ load whatever you choose. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs010><ad3b10001><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecting Doubtful Documents 
desc=Hi, long time no see. I'm sorry to bug you with this big request, despite the pleasure to meet you again. A strange cave was found around Fox Den recently. Several explorers went into the cave with curiosity, but they all escaped with fear, like being possessed by a devil. Later I heard that they've seen horrible things, that were not human. I hoped you would come along and look into the cave. Be prepared for something horrible. If you find some stuff  while eliminating  Werefoxes, please turn back to this village at once and let me know about it. 
runDlg=After the discovery of this cave, the atmosphere in the village became noisy and uneasy. Get rid of this quickly. 
finishDlg=Wow, though this place is so dangerous, you came back here with something. Good job. I'll give you the next mission after examination. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collecting doubtful documents 
desc=Hi, long time no see. Sorry for this big request before sharing our pleasure. A strange cave was found around Fox Den before long. Several explorers had come into the cave with curiosity, but they all escaped with fear, like being possessed by a devil. Later I heard that they's seen horrible things, but not humen. I hope you come here and look into the cave. Be careful for something horrible. If you find some stuff  while eliminating  Werefoxes, please turn back this village and let me know about it without delay. 
runDlg=After the discovery of the cave, an atmosphere of this village is noisy and uneasy. Get rid of them quickly. 
finishDlg=Oh, you come here with something from the dangerous place. Good job. I'll give you next mission after examination. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10001><ad3b10002><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Delivery of Werefox's Tail to Jaime 
desc=According to this document, there was an experiment from there. There are no detailed contents except that the experiment used human bodies. I think really horrible things happened during that experiment. I told Jaime, so if you collect and bring Werefox's tails, Jaime will analyze theml. 
runDlg=You should solve the incident of this dangerous cave as soon as possible. Hurry please.
finishDlg=The lord sent you to me. I heard about you. If you give me the collected stuff, I'll look into that. Please return to the lord right after. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Delivery of Werefox's tail to Jaime 
desc=According to this document, there was an experiment from there. There are no detailed contents except that the experiment used human body. I think horrible things happened from the experiment. I told Jaime, so if you collect and bring Werefox's tails, Jaime will analyze the tail. 
runDlg=You should solve the incident of this dangerous cave as soon as possible. Hurry up.
finishDlg=The lord sent you to me. I heard about you. If you give me the stuff, I'll look into that. Please turn back to the lord. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10002><ad3b10003><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Werefox Elimination
desc=This creature was not formed by nature. This kind of creature can become a big threat to this world. I heard that there was an experiment with human bodies inside the cave. It seems that a man and a fox were combined and both became one as result. The lord confirmed that these creatures are dangerous, so he requested you to  handle this. Go to the cave and eliminate Werefoxes. They should be wiped out without fail. 
runDlg=The dangerous creatures must not go around in this world.
finishDlg=Good job. The Werefoxes were not formed by nature. We had to eliminate them. Even if we feel sorry for their sacrifice. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Werefox Elimination
desc=This creature was not formed by nature. This kind of creature becomes a biggest threat to this world. I heard that there was an experiment of a human body inside the cave. Perhaps it seems that a man and fox are combined and both become one as a result. The lord confirmed how the creature is dangerous, so he requested you  handle this. Go to the cave and eliminate Werefoxes. They should be wiped out without fail. 
runDlg=The dangerous things must not go around this world.
finishDlg=Good job. The Werefoxes was not formed by nature. We would have eliminated them. Even if we are regrettable for their sacrifice.
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10003><ad3b10004><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Guard Werefox's Weapon Collection 
desc=While you talked to Jaime, we received a report in addition. There are Werefoxes who guard  the cave. We decided to call them Guard Werefox. For advancing into the cave, we should eliminate them. At first, by collecting their weapons regardless of the variation of their number, let's prevent them from being armed. The resources inside the cave are limited, so you better go now and take their weapons away. 
runDlg=They'll become much more weaker without their weapons. 
finishDlg=Werefoxes' strength seems to weaken because we took their weapons. Before this risk spread out of the cave, we'll continue to put them under further pressure. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Guard Werefox's weapon Collection 
desc=While you talked to Jaime, we received a report in addition. There are Werefoxes who guard  the cave. We dedide to call them Guard Werefox. For advancing into the cave, we should eliminate them. At first, as collecting their weapons regardless of variation of their number, let's prevent them from being armed. The resource inside the cave is limited, so you'd better take thier weapons. 
runDlg=They'll become weak much more without weapons. 
finishDlg=Werefoxes' strength seems to weaken because we took their weopens. Before the risk comes out of the cave, we'll continue to put pressure. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10004><ad3b10005><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Guard Werefox Elimination 
desc=Owing to too many guards in front of the cave, it is difficult to gain information about the activities inside. Unless we find out information through reconnoitring the inside, we may have troubles by surprise attacks of the enemy. Guard Werefoxes are obstructing our recon. Despite taking weapons and eliminating them, still their number is great. Eliminate as many Guard Werefoxes as possible
runDlg=After getting rid of the guards, I'll send a scout.
finishDlg=Right now, let's reconnoiter. Take a break for a while.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Guard Werefox elimination 
desc=Owing to too many guards in front of the cave, it is difficult to gain the inside information. Unless we find out information through reconnoitering the inside, we may have troubles for enemy's surprise attack. Guard Werefoxes are obstructing our recon. Dispite taking weapons and eliminating them, still their number is great. Eliminate Guard Werefoxes as many as possible
runDlg=After getting rid of guards, I'll make a connaissance.
finishDlg=Right now, let's reconnoiter. Take a break for a while.
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10005><ad3b10006><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Werefox Elimination
Mission2=Guard Werefox Elimination
desc= While you fought with Werefoxes, I was finding out ways to support you. So I ordered skillful people to make some stuff for you. Inow we can start the production and before long the supportive objects will arrive here. Now it's time to start a war against this threat inside the cave. We wiped out the Werefoxes in front of the cave somewhat, but there's no guarantee for safety. Eliminate the rest of the Werefoxes in front, then we can carry out the cave war.
runDlg=Let's slowly move from the front. Things that threaten Cardiff island must be eliminated.
finishDlg=Good job. Ah, the scouts just came back. I'll let you know about new informations. Please wait for a while. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Werefox Elimination
Mission2=Guard Werefox Elimination
desc= While you fight with Werefoxes, I was finding out the way that supports you. So I ordered skillful people to make some stuff for you. If they begin to be made from now, before long support objects will  arrive at. Now it's time to start a war against the threat inside the cave. We wiped out Werefoxes in front somewhat, but there's no guarantee for safety. Eliminate the rest of Werefoxes in front, then we can carry out the cave war.
runDlg=Go forward from the front. Things that threaten Cardiff island must be eliminated.
finishDlg=Good job. Ah, the scouts just came back. I'll let you know about new informations. Please wait for a while. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10006><ad3b10007><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Sick Huge Mole Elimination 
desc=You're here just at the right time. It's been ages since we last met. Because of an emergency, I'll skip the small talk. I investigated the cave from different routes than the lord. People who looked around the cave are saying that they saw strange creatures who sprang up of the earth and obstructed their reconnaissance, so they escaped with hard troubles. There seem to be many strange monsters in this cave. I want you to reveal and report who they are.
runDlg=The cave is teeming with dangerous stuff. Yet I believe you make a good job. 
finishDlg=Could you find out who they are? Huge moles? I am dumbfounded. I'll report the lord about this fact. Please go to the lord. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Sick Huge Mole Elimination 
desc=You're here at just right time. It's been ages since we met. Because of an emergency, I'll skip more greeting. I  looked into the cave in different route from the lord. People who looked into around the cave are saying that they saw strange creatures who sprang up in the earth and obstructed their reconnaissance, so they escaped with hard troubles. There seem to be many strange monsters in the cave. I want you to reveal and report who they are.
runDlg=The cave swarms with dangerous stuff. Yet I believe you make a good job. 
finishDlg=Did you know who they are? Huge moles? I am dumbfounded. I'll report the lord about this fact. Please go to the lord. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10007><ad3b10008><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Sick Huge Mole Elimination 
desc=We don't know how many dangerous creatures resulted from this experiment. Who in the world could have committed such horrible things? Moles as well as foxes were sacrificed. It's also regrettable that humans were victims of this experiment. Yet it can't be helped. But if neglected, the creatures will become a threat to Roxbury one day. I want you to go to the cave and get rid of all Sick Huge Moles. 
runDlg=The results of this experiment gradually becomes a horrible reality. Steel yourself for any thing we don't know yet. 
finishDlg=Moles live underground&#x2026; There may be many moles moles in the earth. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Sick Huge Mole Elimination 
desc=We don't know how many dangerous creatures are sacrificed by experiment. Who committed such horrible things? Moles as well as foxes are sacrified. It's also regrettable that People were sacrificed by experiment. Yet it can't be helped. But if neglected, the creatures will become a threat to Roxbury one day. I want you to go to the cave and get rid of all Sick Huge Moles. 
runDlg=The result of the experiment gradually becomes a horrible reality. Steel yourself for any thing we don't know yet. 
finishDlg=Some moles come in and out the earth&#x2026;there may be many moles in the earth. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10008><ad3b10009><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=The Essence of Unstable Earth Collection
desc=I heard the voice from the spirit of the earth. Weremoles who lived in the cave are digging in and out the earth, so creatures and spirits in the earth are frightened. On account of the Sick Huge Mole's existence, many spirits are nervous. I want you to help them so that they find their peace again. Carry this, earth spirit's pendant. When you eliminate Weremoles, this will help that you gain the Essence of Enstable Earth. Please come to me with this essence. 
runDlg=Because they are harmful to creatures in nature, you should get rid of them quickly. They are the most threatening existence to spirits. 
finishDlg=May the peace be always with the spirits in Cardiff Island&#x2026;thank you.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=The essence of unstable earth Collection
desc=I heard a voice from the spirit of the earth. Weremoles who lived in the cave are coming in and out the earth, so creatures and spirits in the earth are afraid of the thing. On account of Sick Huge Mole's existence, spirits are nervous. I want you to help them so that they find their peace again. Carry this, earth spirit's pendant. When you eliminate Weremoles, this will help that you gain the essence of unstable earth. Please come to me with the essence. 
runDlg=Because they are injurious to creatures in nature, you should get rid of them quickly. They are the most threatening existence to spirits. 
finishDlg=May the peace be always with spirits in Cardiff island&#x2026;thank you.
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10009><ad3b10010><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Whisman Ghoul Elimination
desc=While you eliminated the weremoles, we continued to reconnoiter and I got a terrible report. Even though people who had been used for body experiments died, they are moving around like living things. It's really terrible. Both not living and not dead things go around the cave. Conquer your fear and eliminate Whisman Ghouls. 
runDlg=I can't believe Noble Masquer made the experiments on this human bodies.
finishDlg=Good job. Let's continue to proceed to the next task.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Whisman Ghoul Elimination
desc=While you eliminate the weremoles, we continued to reconnoiter. After reconnaissance, I got a terrible report. Even though the people who had been used for body experiment died, they are moving around like living things. It's really terrible. Both no living and no dead things go around the cave. Conquer your fear and eliminate Whisman Ghouls. 
runDlg=I can't believe Noble Masquer made the experiment on a human body.
finishDlg=Good job. Let's continue to proceed to the next.
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10010><ad3b10011><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Hagdis Zombie Elimination 
desc=The more we go into it, the more dangerous is this cave. I don't know by what influence of human experiments they changed this way. But this job should be finished quickly. Make an effort day and night until all these things are wiped out. I only believe in you.
runDlg=What a gloomy dawn!  For the Living Dead&#x2026;.
finishDlg=You did this dangerous job well. I asked a favor to Jaime. Go to Jaime at once. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hagdis Zombie Elimination 
desc=The more we go into, the more dangerous is this cave. I don't know if they changed in this way by what influence of human experiment. But this job should be finished quickly. Make an effort day and night until all these things are wiped out. I only believe you.
runDlg=What a groomy dawn! Living corpses are&#x2026;.
finishDlg=You did dangerous things well. I asked a favor to Jaime. Go to Jaime at once. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10011><ad3b10012><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Whisman Ghoul's  Bone Collection 
Mission2=Whisman Zombie's  Bone Collection 
desc=These things are living corpses. Their brain and spirit already died but the body is alive. We should reveal who is the real supervisor of this experiment. Then we can turn them back to nature. Eliminate Whisman Ghoul and Whisman Zombie and collect their bones. I will put great effort in this to uncover the cause. 
runDlg=It's horrible that these corpses still move around. 
finishDlg=Thank you for your effort. Let's discover the cause through the spirit's voice. The lord calls for you. Go to him.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Whisman Ghoul's  bone collection 
Mission2=Whisman Ghoul's bone collection 
desc=The things are living corpses. Their brain and spirit already died but body is alive. We should reveal who is the real supervisor of this experiment. Then we can turn back to nature. Eliminate Whisman Ghoul and Whisman Ghoul Zombie and collect their bones. With a great effort, I'll uncover the cause. 
runDlg=Corpses go around? It's horrible. 
finishDlg=Thank you for your effort. Let's discover the cause through spirit's voice. The lord calls out you. Go to him.
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10012><ad3b10013><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Hagdis Ghoul Elimination 
desc=Another kind of corpses were found besides Whisman corpses. Hagdis tribe's corpses also are going around alive. The corpses resulted through experiment are no small number. You should wipe out these horrible corpses. Right now go to the cave and get rid of Hagdis Ghouls. 
runDlg=Hagdis Ghoul is also dangerous. Please take care of yourself.
finishDlg=Good job. It's most likely, we come to the end of this cave now. With a little extra effort, we'll make a result. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hagdis Ghoul Elimination 
desc=Another kind of corpses were found besides Whisman corpses. Hagdis tribe's corpses also are going around alive. Corpses made by experiment is no small number. You should wipe out the horrible corpses. Right now go to the cave and get rid of Hagdis Ghouls. 
runDlg=Hagdis Ghoul is also dangerous. Please take care of yourself.
finishDlg=Good job. Likely to come to the end of this cave now. With a little extra effort, we'll make a result. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10013><ad3b10014><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Hagdis Zombie Elimination 
desc=Jaime said that there must be a powerful wizard in the back of the ghoul and zombie groups. We don't know yet who he is. But we'll come to know by Jaime, after a bit more of investigation. You have to eliminate Hagdis Zombies as well as Hagdis Ghouls. At first eliminate Hagdis Zombies for convient investigation. 
runDlg=The end of this cave seems to be seen. Exploration will be easier by eliminating the dangerous Hagdis Zombies. 
finishDlg=Now, there is a result  to Jaime's investigation. Go to Jaime.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hagdis Zombie Elimination 
desc=Jaime said that there is a powerful wizard in the back of ghoul and zombie group. We don't know yet who he is, but we'll come to know, by Jaime, after a bit more of investigation. You have to eliminate Hagdis Zombies as well as Hagdis Ghouls. Eliminate Hagdis Zombies for convient investigation. 
runDlg=The end of this cave seems to be seen. Exploration will be easier as eliminating the dangerous Hagdis Zombies. 
finishDlg=Now, there is a result  about Jaime's investigation. Go to Jaime.
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10014><ad3b10015><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Hagdis Ghoul's Bone Collection 
Mission2=Hagdis Zombie's Bone Collection 
desc=Through the bones you had brought me, I found out which experiment  it is and which result was formed. The Wizard who had carried out the experiment died a long time ago. But as for this result, he seems to be still alive. It was thought that who was called Black Wizard, had done body experiments. Because of the experiment in the group of Noble Masquer, Black Wizard was exiled. Now he is staying in Cardiff Island. But I am wondering how he can't be dead, despite being buried alive. Go to the cave again and bring Hagdis Ghoul and Hagdis Zombie's bones. Through investigation of them, we confirm how he can be alive.
runDlg=It's surprising. He is still alive! 
finishDlg=You bring them very well. I'll make a short survey. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hagdis Ghoul's Bone collection 
Mission2=Hagdis Zombie's Bone Collection 
desc=Through the bone you had given me, I found which experiment  it is and which result was formed. Wizard who had carried out the experiment died a long time ago. But as for this result, he seems to be still alive. It is thought that who called Black Wizard, had done body experiment. Because of the experiment in the group of Noble Masquer, Black Wizard was exiled. Now he is staying in Cardiff island. But I am wondering how he can't be dead, despite being buried alive. Go to the cave again and bring Hagdis Ghoul and Hagdis Zombie's bones. Through investigation of them, we confirm how to be alive.
runDlg=It's surprising. He has lived till now! 
finishDlg=You bring them very well. I'll look into them for a while. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10015><ad3b10016><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Conversation with Lord Lionel
desc=My god! It's terrible. Black Wizard changed himself into Lich. While being buried and trying to escape, probably he ate something he experimented with. Report this fact to the lord. 
runDlg=It's really dangerous. Go ahead to the lord. 
finishDlg=What? Did you say Black Wizard turned into Lich and is still alive?  Black Wizard is alive yet! At first I'll consult Roderick about this. Prepare for Black Wizard's elimination right now. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conservation with Sir Raionel
desc=My god! It's terrible. Black Wizard changed himself into Lich. While being buried and trying to escape, probably he ate something he experimented. Report this fact to the lord. 
runDlg=It's a dangerous thing. Go ahead to the lord. 
finishDlg=What? Did you say Black Wizard turned into Leach and still alive?  Black Wizard is alive yet! At first I'll consult Roderick about this. Prepare for Black Wizard's elimination right now. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10016><ad3b10017><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Black Wizard Elimination 
desc=Roderick says that he was exiled because of carrying out experiments on a human body in the past. What an unpardonable experiment it is! Here is the spot where a group brought Black Wizard and buried him alive. Now we should finish this long, long curse. Go get rid of Black Wizard. 
runDlg=I wish you good luck. 
finishDlg=Roderick and I'll settle this incident. It's a relieve that people besides these villagers don't know about this. I wish you to keep quiet about it in other villages too. I'll give a great reward for your great achievement. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Black Wizard Elimination 
desc=Roderick says that he was exiled because of carrying out the experiment on a human body in the past. How unpardonable experiment it is! Here is the spot which a group with Black Wizard was exiled. Now we should finish this long, long curse. Go get rid of Black Wizard. 
runDlg=I wish you good luck. 
finishDlg=Roderick and I'll settle this incident. It's a relieve that people besides this villagers don't still know. I wish you too don't say this thing in other village. I'll give a great reward for your great achievement. 
</newversion></questtextxml></ad3b10017><ad3b10018><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Sick Huge Mole Elimination 
desc= On my investigation, these moles need to be treated. I have asked spirits about these moles before. That time I thought they only were dangerous. But now I know that because they were sick, such things happened.  I'll give you this stone. This, called 'natural forces', has an ability that is able to heal sick creatures. If you eliminate the moles, this stone will send back them to nature. 
runDlg=May you return the sick animals to the bosom of nature...
finishDlg=You performed a difficult job well. Once more you turned back the poor animals to nature. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Sick Huge Mole Elimination 
desc= On my investigation, these moles need to be treated. I have ever asked spirits about these moles before, that time I thought they only were dangerous. But now I know that because they were sick, such things happened.  I'll give this. This stone called 'natural forces' has an ability that is able to heal sick creatures. If you eliminate the moles, this stone will send back them to nature. 
